HEADWORD: Infecund
<hw>In*fec"und</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>infecundus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>inf⟦eacute⟧cond</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Fecund</er>.]</ety> <def>Unfruitful; not
producing young; barren; infertile.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
